  "original_title": "Sri Lanka govt security yields slightly up in dull trade",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka govt security yields slightly up in dull trade",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka\u2019s risk free treasury bond and bill yields closed slightly up in dull trade on Monday while a guidance peg on interbank spot trading strengthened slightly, dealers said.",
        "A bond maturing on 01.06.25 closed at 25.00/30 percent up from 24.80/25.00 percent at last closing.",
        "A guidance peg announced by Sri Lanka\u2019s central bank for interbank transactions strengthened by 21 cents to 361.09 against the US dollar on July 25 from the previous 361.30 rupees last week, data showed on Friday.",
        "Commercial banks offered dollars for telegraphic transfers at rates between 368.09 and 370.00 for small transactions on July 25, steady from last week, data showed.",
        "Banks offered to buy inward remittances at 358.09 -359.00 rupees, also steady from the previous close. (Colombo/July 25/2022)"
      ],
